== '''Universal Changes''' ==
* '''Drive Parry'''
** Fixed issue where {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}} could not be performed at certain timings after parrying an attack, causing the player to be locked into their parry recovery animation when attempting a punish
* '''Input Buffer'''
** If the opponent's {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}} freeze overlaps with a downed character's wakeup input buffer window, the buffer timing will be reduced from 10f → 7f
** This change was made due to issues caused by the previous patch [[Street_Fighter_6/Version/2.02|(Version 2.02)]] which increased the wakeup input buffer by 3 frames
* '''Modern Controls'''
** Fixed issue where after certain airborne moves (e.g. Dhalsim's Yoga Float, Rashid's Wing Stroke), if the opponent activated {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}}, the airborne character could not use air normals with the Auto button for a short time
<br>

== '''Character Changes''' ==

=== '''JP''' ===
* {{clr|H|Departure: Shadow}} (214P/{{clr|OD|PP}}~{{clr|H|214HP}})
** Fixed issue where the startup was 1 frame faster when canceled into from {{clr|L|2LK}}, {{clr|M|5MP}}, {{clr|M|2MK}}, or {{clr|H|5HK}}
<br>

=== '''M. Bison''' ===
* Devil Reverse + Psycho Mine ([2]8K~P + Mine)
** Fixed issue where the Psycho Mine would stay embedded if a {{clr|DR|Drive Reversal}} was performed after blocking the 2nd hit
* Devil Reverse + Psycho Mine ([2]8K/{{clr|OD|KK}}~P + Mine) / Somersault Skull Diver ([2]8K/{{clr|OD|KK}}~K~P + Mine)
** Fixed issue where the attack could not hit from behind under some circumstances, causing M. Bison to whiff through the opponent's body
<br>